      "ia": "IO a — a description (recipe) of a side-effectful computation. Nothing has run yet.",
      "f": "(a ⟶ IO b) — given result a, constructs the next IO action description",
      "exec_a": "Execute ia: the runtime runs the described effect and produces value a. Real I/O happens here.",
      "a": "a — the value obtained by running ia (e.g. a String read from stdin)",
      "build": "Apply f(a): build the next IO action description. No effect yet — only the description is created.",
      "ib": "IO b — the description of the second effect, constructed from a",
      "exec_b": "Execute IO b: the runtime runs the second described effect. Effects of ia happened BEFORE this.",
      "b": "b — the final result. The sequencing of exec_a before exec_b is the entire bind contract."
    },
    "title": "IO bind: execute ia, feed a to f to build IO b, execute IO b — also called: .then (Promises), >>=",
